Hello everyone!

Just wanted to see if there's any interest in adding this function to lodash. It is like _.once, except if the function call throws, it gets "another chance" to run.

An example implementation:

```
function onceUnlessThrows(func, onFail = () => {}) {
	let threw = true;

	return (...args) => {
		if (!threw) return;

		try {
			func(...args);
			threw = false;
		} catch (e) {
			onFail();
		}
	};
}
```

